\par \pard\plain \s6\li360\sa31 \f2\fs16 The object of TicTactics is to be the first player to line up three playing pieces in a row, horizontally, vertically, or diagonally.  In the 4x4x4 game, you 
must line up four pieces in a row.  The following section explains how to play the game.
\par 
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Choose a Board Type:
\par \pard\plain \s7\fi-360\li720\sa180\tx720 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab From the Game menu, choose the type of board you want:  3x3, 3x3x3, or 4x4x4.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Choose a Skill Level:
\par \pard\plain \s7\fi-360\li720\sa180\tx720 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab From the Options menu, choose Beginner, Intermediate, or Expert.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Start a New Game:
\par \pard\plain \s21\li360\sa180\tx720 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab From the Game menu, choose New, or press F2.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Occupy a Square:
\par \pard\plain \s7\fi-360\li720\sa180\tx720 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab Move the pointer to the desired location, and click the left mouse button.
