\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 TicTactics Rules:
\par \pard\plain \s7\fi-360\li720\sa180\tx720 \f2\fs16 \{bmc bull.bmp\}\tab The game board is a 3x3, 3x3x3, or 4x4x4 grid of squares.
\par \{bmc bull.bmp\}\tab To win, you must line up three pieces in a row: horizontally, vertically, or diagonally.  In the 4x4x4 game, you must line up four pieces in a row.
\par \{bmc bull.bmp\}\tab During your turn, you can occupy any {\ul free square.}{\v FreeSquare}
\par \{bmc bull.bmp\}\tab Players alternate taking turns until either one player wins or no free squares remain.  If neither player wins, the game is a draw.
\par \pard\plain \s17\li360\sb60\sa187 \f2\fs16 {\cf6 Note:}  The opponent's piece is always red.  If you do not have a color monitor, red balls appear solid and blue balls appear patterned.
